data.name: HelpCommandModule_SendQueryHelp_Description
data.value:
You can create queries by combining operations and filters.
For example: `{0}sg n:5 d:3 y:1995-2005` to start a session with 5 rounds of anime on hard difficulty between the years 1995 and 2005.

data.name: HelpCommandModule_SendQueryHelp_Operations_Description
data.value: `n:` - Number of rounds to play in a session (max 10) `im:` - Image manipulation: pixelated `im:p`, inverted `im:i`, oil-painted `im:o`, grayscale `im:g`, flipped vertically `im:f` or multiple `im:p,i,o,g,f` (any combination) `nh:` - Do not show hints `nh:1` `aggr:` - Change aggregation method when using anime lists: all combined `aggr:union`, present in all lists `aggr:intersect` or equal sample size per list `aggr:balance` (default)

data.name: RequireNonHentai_Error
data.value: This feature is not available on this bot.

data.name: HelpCommandModule_SendQueryHelp_Filters_Description
data.value: `d:` - Difficulty `d:0` to `d:5` (`0` disables difficulty filter) `y:` - Year `y:2010` or year range `y:1995-2005` `g:` - Genre `g:action` or multiple `g:action,-sliceoflife,!kids`, where `-` or `!` excludes the genre (use `{0}genres` for all genres) `t:` - Type of song: openings `t:op`, endings `t:ed` or insert songs `t:in` (`in` works with `sga` only) `sl:` - Sample length in seconds, between 5 and 30 (only usable with `{0}sgsa`) `mal:` - MyAnimeList user anime list `mal:username` or multiple `mal:user1,user2` `anilist:` - AniList user anime list `anilist:username` or multiple `anilist:user1,user2`
